xv6 Large File System (Lab 3 - Task 1)

This repository contains the solution for extending the xv6 file system to support large files (up to ~64MB) using doubly-indirect blocks.

Overview

By default, xv6 limits files to 268 blocks (12 direct, 1 singly-indirect). This project modifies the inode structure to support:

11 Direct blocks

1 Singly-indirect block

1 Doubly-indirect block

This increases the maximum file size to 65,803 blocks (11 + 256 + 256^2).

Repository Structure

headers_setup.md: Contains the mandatory changes to param.h, fs.h, and file.h.

fs_variations.md: Contains 10 different variations of implementing the bmap() and itrunc() logic in fs.c. These range from standard academic implementations to highly optimized bitwise versions.

How to use

Apply the header changes to your local xv6 source code.

Choose ONE of the 10 variations from fs_variations.md and replace the bmap() and itrunc() functions in your kernel/fs.c.

Add $U/_bigfile\ to your Makefile under UPROGS.

Run make clean && make qemu and test using the bigfile user command.